indicators are further proposed, including road, railway and inland waterway container ratios. Based on the existing port statistics, the measurement methods for all proposed indicators are put forward. Finally, the main gaps between domestic and abroad port collecting and distributing system are discussed by comparison of evaluation indicators. Some policy suggestions are put forward from aspects of improving the statistical system and developing rail-water intermodal transport and transshipment. Keywords: Container; Collection and distribution system; Evaluation indicator; Sea-rail combined transportation; Transshipment

